<section xml:id="commenting-out-items-in-editors" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                            xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                            xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Commenting out items in editors</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId" xml:id="commenting-out-items-in-editors.guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId">Test Case Editor</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="testSuiteEditorContextId" xml:id="commenting-out-items-in-editors.testSuiteEditorContextId">Test Suite Editor</anchor>
  <para>
    In the Test Case Editor and the Test Suite Editor, you can
    deactivate and reactivate Test Cases and Test Steps.
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select the Test Steps or Test Cases you want to deactivate and select:
      </para>
      
      <para>
        <emphasis role="menuPath">Set as active / inactive</emphasis>
      </para>
      
      <para>
        from the context menu.
      </para>
      
      <para role="tip">
        You can also use <emphasis role="input">»CTRL+7«</emphasis> to toggle the items as active or inactive.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The items you selected will be set as inactive. They are
        shown with green text and the sign <literal>//</literal>
        before the Test Case or Test Step name.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Any inactive items are not considered in Test Suite
        validation, nor are they executed during a test run.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        You can reactivate the items by selecting:
      </para>
      
      <para>
        <emphasis role="menuPath">Set as active / inactive</emphasis>
      </para>
      
      <para>
        from the context menu.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>